        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 54,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2010-12-16T12:35:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m pretty sure this isn\u0027t the best way to implement this. Instead, you should have a queue of pending FBUpdateMessage to send to a single AsyncWriter (you can\u0027t assume that each update message is sent to the client before another one comes in, so a queue is necessary).\n\nThe corefb_io_func() should simply try to called asyncWriter_write() as long as there are queue update messages.\n\nWhenever you add a new update message to an empty queue, simply call asyncWriter_init() + asyncWriter_write().\n\nBonus points if you can merge updates in the queue when they overlap (but this is stricly optional)",
      "revId": "d19efd0d8157e6b26b507cb74c8f8cf72cb8a584",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
